# Job results page — UI/UX standards

When editing any saved-jobs UI (`job-results-page`, `job-result-card`, `job-result-detail`, interview editors), follow the full transformation prompt in `.cursor/ui-ux/ui-ux.md`.

## Scope

- Preserve all facade bindings, event handlers, routes, and accessibility behavior.
- Refactor structure, spacing, hierarchy, and styling only.
- Use existing design tokens from `src/styles.scss` (`--app-*`).

## Page structure (top → bottom)

1. **Header** — title, short description, secondary refresh + last-updated metadata
2. **Overview** — stats cards when no filters are active
3. **Priority strip** — featured jobs needing review or with interviews
4. **Toolbar** — search, source, sort, workflow chips, filter summary
5. **Workspace** — list + detail split panel

## Visual rules

- One filled primary CTA per screen state (empty → search link; otherwise actions live in detail panel).
- Refresh and filter actions are secondary (outline/ghost), not gradient-filled.
- Increase whitespace; group controls in a single toolbar card.
- Avoid duplicate filter summaries on the same view.
- Prefer calm surfaces, subtle borders, and clear type hierarchy over dense admin-panel layouts.
